-- Hewlett-Packard Will Pay Former CEO Mark Hurd Severance of $12.2 Million
-- Greg Chang
-- 2010-08-06T21:36:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-06/hewlett-packard-to-pay-hurd-severance-of-12-2-million.html

          
          
             Hewlett-Packard Co. said Mark Hurd,
who is stepping down as chairman and chief executive officer,
will receive a severance payment of $12.2 million.  
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                           
                 
                 
                                       
                                   
               
                        
           
                          Aug. 6 (Bloomberg) -- David Garrity, principal at GVA Research LLC, discusses the outlook for Hewlett-Packard Co. after Chief Executive Officer Mark Hurd announced his resignation. 
     Hurd resigned after an investigation found he had a personal relationship with a contractor who received pay from the company that wasn’t business-related. Garrity talks with Pimm Fox on Bloomberg Television's "Taking Stock." (Source: Bloomberg)  
                   
    

                 
           
                           
                 
                 
                                       
                                   
               
                        
           
                          Aug. 6 (Bloomberg) -- Aaron Rakers, an analyst at Stifel Nicolaus & Co., talks with Bloomberg's Lizzie O'Leary and Matt Miller about today's resignation by Hewlett-Packard Co. Chief Executive Officer Mark Hurd and the outlook for the company.
     Hurd resigned as CEO after an investigation found he had a personal relationship with a contractor who received pay from the company that wasn’t business-related. Chief Financial Officer Cathie Lesjak will take over as interim CEO. (Source: Bloomberg)  
                           

     
